					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">I never thought of any use for frame IRQ.  It would trigger sometimes during vblank, wouldn't it?  No way anyone would want that interrupted.  So for music you'd end up with little pauses in the music playback (very brief ones, but I can't imagine it helping anything).
<br />
<br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">That will call the normal (NTSC) play routine 1 extra time every 5 frames, effectivily making the music 1.2x faster (changing ~50Hz to ~60Hz) </div>
<br />
<br />That burns up CPU cycles though.  In the worst case, the sound frames that take longer to process than the others will get called twice.
<br />
<br />A better way, I think would be to use fixed-point counts for the tempo.  Then it would be pretty trivial to adjust it for NTSC/PAL and still run the code once per frame, just adjust some equations.  Same thing applies to the rest of a game too, just that it becomes less trivial to cover everything.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

						<table width="100%" cellspacing="0">
						<tr valign="middle">
							<td class="gensmall" align="right">
							
							</td>
						</tr>
						</table>
					</td>
				</tr>
				</table>
			</td>
		</tr>

